  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3060474016" />
    <a title="Ivana Books Are Magic" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/56173179-ivana-books-are-magic"><img alt="Ivana Books Are Magic" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1578249636p2/56173179.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3060474016?book_show_action=true">Nov 24, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ivana Books Are Magic" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ivana Books Are Magic" href="/user/show/56173179-ivana-books-are-magic">Ivana Books Are Magic</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3060474016" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17454217095575036211">The Baron in the Trees reads like a fairy-tale, but one with modern touches that include sophisticated satire and parody. In a nutshell, this novel is a story of a young baron who decides to live in the trees. The novel itself is narrated by the younger brother of the baron Cosimo. Besides describing Cosimo to us, the narrator does a great job of portraying his family members and other characters as well. <br/><br/>Cosimo, the hero of the book, climbs a tree after having quarreled with his father, vowing </span>
  <span id="freeText17454217095575036211" style="display:none">The Baron in the Trees reads like a fairy-tale, but one with modern touches that include sophisticated satire and parody. In a nutshell, this novel is a story of a young baron who decides to live in the trees. The novel itself is narrated by the younger brother of the baron Cosimo. Besides describing Cosimo to us, the narrator does a great job of portraying his family members and other characters as well. <br /><br />Cosimo, the hero of the book, climbs a tree after having quarreled with his father, vowing to never set put on earth again. Cosimo keeps his promise and soon becomes famous for it. There is also a story of love to be told and before the novel ends we will see a lot of twists and turns in this love story. All in all, I quite liked this book. It is original, well written, sad at times but also wonderfully funny. I can understand why this novel has reached such a cult status in Italy. <br /><br />I listen to an audio version of this book twice (or perhaps even more) and enjoyed it every time. The melodic quality of Italian language makes it ideal for audio books. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17454217095575036211" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


