  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3207398083" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3207398083" />
    <a title="Ali Karimnejad" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/93895577-ali-karimnejad"><img alt="Ali Karimnejad" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591439739p2/93895577.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3207398083?book_show_action=true">Feb 27, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ali Karimnejad" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ali Karimnejad" href="/user/show/93895577-ali-karimnejad">Ali Karimnejad</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9789643510176" href="/book/show/1032098._">review of another edition</a>


        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3207398083" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17619409022861331146">&quot;The Baron in the Trees&quot; not only couldn&apos;t satisfy me as an adult guy, but also for the teenagers I doubt it would be an appropriate book. not because our main character rebels and escapes from home, but because Cosimo, decides to climb up the trees and be there for the rest of his life only because he decided to do so. <br/><br/>I think something here has been really messed up and it is &quot;what makes Cosimo a great man?&quot; what will be remembered about him? In the way the book narrates the story, all the foc</span>
  <span id="freeText17619409022861331146" style="display:none">"The Baron in the Trees" not only couldn't satisfy me as an adult guy, but also for the teenagers I doubt it would be an appropriate book. not because our main character rebels and escapes from home, but because Cosimo, decides to climb up the trees and be there for the rest of his life only because he decided to do so. <br /><br />I think something here has been really messed up and it is "what makes Cosimo a great man?" what will be remembered about him? In the way the book narrates the story, all the focus is on being up the trees. Cosimo takes an oath to never put his foot on the ground and he pays hefty prices for that. but he never breaks his oath. Is it something we should admire?! Should we read this story for our children? I don't think so. Cosimo is the hero because of other characteristics he have and they never get fair attention. instead, it is keeping his word that is mentioned over and over. There is no doubt that keeping your word is praiseworthy but one should never forget to step back from his wrong decisions, or unnecessary actions that hinders his life. Couldn't Cosimo be a great man if he put his foot on the ground? In this way, I found Cosimo a stubborn guy. although it is wrapped in beautiful words. <br /><br />we may argue that ground is a symbol of all restrictions and the trees are a symbol of freedom. and all the efforts Cosimo puts in order to avoid the ground is because he wants to be free. but unfortunately this is not the case as we never read about supernatural characteristics of the trees or any metaphors about them. all said about trees are just their names: Walnut, Oak, Fig, Cherry, etc. <br /><br />to conclude, While "The Baron on the Trees" has a novel idea and very good material, it fails to make a good story for younger ages and for myself, it lacks many things. but still I liked the way it ended.<br /><br />پا فشاری بیش از حد روی یک حرف، فرقی با ایمان تزلزل ناپذیر اهالی کلیسا نداره. نمی فهمم چطور نویسنده روی درخت بودن کازیمو به هر قیمتی رو ستایش می کنه اما به راهب ها می توپه. انسانی که دنده عقب نداشته باشه از آدمیت دور میشه. به نظرم کتاب نتونست پتانسیل بالایی رو که داشت بالفعل کنه و ایده کتاب تلف شد.<br />با این حال یک جمله ای داشت که یادگاری از این کتاب باسم می مونه: <br />«بسیار دیده شده است که مردمانی که برای آرمانی نه چندان روشن و مشخص مبارزه می کنند مجبورند برای جبران گنگی و سستی انگیزه هایشان ظاهری بسیار جدی به خود بدهند.»</span>
  <a data-text-id="17619409022861331146" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


